		<td><b>Speaking of polarity... (APU related)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In the APU, what are the conditions to output a sample of &quot;silence&quot; (zero) instead of a &quot;volume level&quot; (non zero), including the duty cycles (0 and 1) but as negative and positive?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>rainwarrior</b> [ Tue Jul 15, 2014 6:38 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Speaking of polarity... (APU related)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The initial output is always zero to positive, there's no negative. After this it goes to a highpass filter, which will centre a playing waveform around zero a little bit after its onset, and when it stops playing it will drift back up to the zero line.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
